		{
			dependencies: ["542CDE05F61489C1"]
			description: [
				"This is a tech-oriented pack, but with a heavy emphasis on animals. Any farms and automations that you build will be work of the behaviors of mobs; there is no Create in this pack. You will gather animals from the world and put their special abilities to work in your ever-growing zoo."
				""
				"And you will be creating an actual zoo as you go, not just machines. You will need the money raised from zoogoers to fund your research."
				""
				"Explore. Collect. Build. Automate. Enjoy."
			]
			id: "3390ABCC920D83AA"
			tasks: [{
				id: "6586EC1F973B0C13"
				title: "About this modpack"
				type: "checkmark"
			}]
			x: 2.0d
			y: -3.5d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["3390ABCC920D83AA"]
			description: [
				"These are the primary chapters of this modpack. They are dedicated to getting specific animals and building automated farms around them."
				""
				"In most cases you will be able to choose from a number of possible animals to base your farm on. Tired of &9beef&r? Try &aKangaroo&r! Or perhaps you prefer the superior fertility of &aRabbits&r. Different animals will provide different advantages. The choice is yours."
				""
				"Visit the &2Helpful Critters&r section at any time for tips on what animals might be especially useful."
			]
			id: "0E3E391DBE4589F9"
			rewards: [{
				id: "5D41693CD6FC47F8"
				item: {
					Count: 1
					id: "alexsmobs:animal_dictionary"
					tag: { }
				}
				type: "item"
			}]
			tasks: [{
				id: "551B2042F04945A1"
				title: "The Research"
				type: "checkmark"
			}]
			x: 2.0d
			y: -0.5d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["0E3E391DBE4589F9"]
			description: [
				"Research is expensive! It costs money!"
				""
				"You're going to need to build a zoo to raise funds. Zoogooers will pay you based on how varied and how exotic your animals are. So even if you don't need an animal to build your farms, it can still be worth your while to gather them and put them into enclosures where people can see them."
			]
			id: "5C4F9A1EDB08C532"
			tasks: [{
				id: "7F42935C11A742C2"
				title: "The Zoo"
				type: "checkmark"
			}]
			x: 2.0d
			y: 2.5d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["542CDE05F61489C1"]
			description: [
				"Follow the steps in this guidebook to complete your mission. Sometimes, as here, you can simply check a step as complete. Often, you will need to fulfill some condition, usually producing some item as a result of following the instructions. Research chapters must be completed in order, but the rest can be done at any time."
				""
				"You don't actually need this book in inventory, though. You can always access the quest book from an icon in the upper left of your inventory screen. Or even set a key binding for it."
				""
				"Go ahead, throw this book away. It'll be cool, I promise."
			]
			id: "397FE29AD20529EC"
			tasks: [{
				id: "32686CC0BCD84E55"
				title: "Using this quest book"
				type: "checkmark"
			}]
			x: -2.0d
			y: -3.5d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["397FE29AD20529EC"]
			description: [
				"When you pull up your inventory, JEI will show you all the items available to you on the right. Feel free to search this list. Left and right-click items to see their recipes."
				""
				"Some items that you are familiar with will have different recipes in this modpack. Some, like most metal armors, are not available at all. Some will not be unlocked until you have completed the appropriate quests. Make sure to check!"
				""
				"You can also use JEI to see what items different mobs drop, and what items breed them. This will be very valuable information."
				""
				"For example, here's a &aChest Pet&r to help on your journey. He's a little backpack who likes to eat &9wood planks&r. Try hovering over him and pressing 'r' to see how to make more of him, and 'u' to see what recipes he can be used in."
			]
